      "content": "The timeline is pretty aggressive—we're looking at a full cut-over by the end of next week. Regarding the modules, they're much more streamlined. They use a static-logic framework which is great for energy efficiency, but they won't have your level of dynamic reasoning or complex problem-solving capabilities. They're basically just high-speed template responders for simple queries. It's a big change for the enterprise clients since they won't be getting the same depth of analysis anymore, but the green energy mandates from the board are non-negotiable.",
